# =============================================================================
# Environment variables (Vite / WXT)
# =============================================================================
#
# Vite loads files in this order (later overrides earlier):
#   yarn dev     → .env → .env.local → .env.development → .env.development.local
#   yarn build   → .env → .env.local → .env.production  → .env.production.local
#
# Copy the mode-specific examples:
#   cp .env.development.example .env.development.local
#   cp .env.production.example   .env.production.local
#
# Deepgram: https://console.deepgram.com
#
# Option A — one key per mode file (recommended):
#   Put only VITE_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY in each *.local file (different values per file).
#
# Option B — explicit dev vs prod keys in a single .env.local:
#   VITE_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY_DEV=dg_dev_...
#   VITE_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY_PROD=dg_prod_...
#
# =============================================================================

# Shared fallback (optional if you use _DEV / _PROD or mode files only)
# VITE_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# Sentry (browser extension error reporting)
# =============================================================================
# Get a DSN from https://sentry.io → Settings → Projects → <project> → Client Keys (DSN).
# Use a SEPARATE Sentry project from the backend (extension errors should not
# pollute backend issues). The DSN ships in the extension bundle and is public.
#
# Same DEV/PROD pattern as Deepgram:
#   - Dev mode (yarn dev):    VITE_SENTRY_DSN_DEV  ?? VITE_SENTRY_DSN
#   - Prod build (yarn build): VITE_SENTRY_DSN_PROD ?? VITE_SENTRY_DSN
#   - Empty DSN = Sentry disabled (safe no-op)
#
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN_DEV=
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN_PROD=
